node.text:
REALTORS-LENDERS-TITLE REPS - This virtual event is for you! Read On↘️⬇️⬇️⁣
⁣
If 2020 taught you anything at all... it's that you can no longer be INVISIBLE 👀 online. When a market shuts off (physically) due to a lockdown, shock, etc. - there is one thing that will not follow those rules, and that is a BRAND 💪🏼 . It keeps working when you aren't always allowed to.⁣
⁣
✅ If you have one, this event will help you learn strategies and practices to do it BETTER.⁣
✅ If you don't have one, you will hear why it's now or never for creating one and where to start.⁣
⁣
🎟 Ticket sales will support @nokidhungry and can be bought via the link in my bio!⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
_____________________⁣
@vanguardproperties @corcorangloballiving @polarisrealty @ascent.re @sfassociationofrealtors @acmerealestate @house.of.kinoko @chelsea.peitz @liznovello @iammegananderson @shivpeter @caitlinhenning @bermanmediasocial @brandtegic

node.text:
Earlier this summer ☀️, I got to put together a cool mini-project with @socialwaycreative and @tomtran22 at the famous and historic "Hamilton" building 🏢 in downtown SF. ⁣
⁣
They mayor 👨‍💼 of the building, @tcatch58, who is a dear friend and long time resident there, was generous to share it all with us. ⁣
⁣
Great piece of history and a fun way to dynamically showcase a real estate project via video 🎥. You didn't just "show" us this place, but rather shared it with amazing context throughout!  Thank you, Tom.

node.text:
⁣Plenty of people looking to make sales or push agenda.  Over these last few months where more eyeballs and brains have been consuming record amounts of content, we can now see who is genuinely trying to help and give, as opposed to asking and selling.  Some people I am close to I wanted to shout out in this video! ⁣⁣⬇️⬇️
⁣⁣
Fitness space (online) is filled with so many people putting out great stuff to help everyone workout out at home and more creatively.  My Rumble friends of @therealajperez, @colbyclaire, and @julialstern are some of the best out there and always eager to help those in need of fitness guidance. ⁣⁣💪🏽
⁣⁣
My big brother, @seerenespeak is one of the very best at what he does in development and influence.  @sgeller86 is an attorney here in they Bay Area that is also a boss at his own craft and game, helping people navigate through mistakes they might or have made that could impact their lives. 👊🏽
⁣⁣
Savvy marketers like @thekeywithsydney, @brandtegic, and @socialwaycreative are helping people with high level courses and marketing advice - for nothing. 🌐  Needless to see, this is more important than ever to have a brand and know how to push it. ⁣⁣ In the real estate space, my siblings @shivpeter and @neelhome absolutely KILL it with advice to consumers and members of the real estate community on how to be better online. 💻
⁣⁣
All given away, never asking for anything in return, just building community and support.  Bravo guys and thanks for all you do.  We all appreciate you! 👏🏽👏🏽 @doyourumble @motivationmafia @thehustledaily

node.text:
We see a lot of people selling services, others are gouging consumers.  Some are giving away free advice, offering help and assurances🙏🏼. There are also some that are just fishing for a sale 🤮.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If you had any REAL value to offer in what you do, its already been obvious to you and how you have operated these last few months.  If you didn't, you have been trying to figure 🤔 it out and while that might be hard - the easiest way to offer up something useful to others is the thing everyone needs more of - hope, positivity, clarity, concern, empathy. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Rockstar 💣 Miami agent @mariacamila_miami  is leading 🚀 in her market not by trying to sell or offer you a home right now, but through simple compassion. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
☑️ Check out our entire chat via the link in my bio!  Enjoyed catching up with her and learning how she is giving back in such simple but impactful 👊🏼ways to her market. ⁣
⁣
@miami__realestate @lifemiamibeach @meganprobst_compass

node.text:
For so many living in high-cost markets, the decision to abandon a great rent controlled situation in exchange for something that will cost much more but be half of the size.....is a head scratcher. 🤔⁣
⁣
Sometimes a better idea can be to buy a 2nd home AS your 1st home.  Wait, what?! Many clients did this last year and the investment has paid off quite well. 🚀🔥💲⁣
⁣
Millennials here in the Bay Area spend weekends in Utah, or Lake Tahoe (for example) enough of the year that it could make a lot of sense to buy a vacation property there.  Best of all, it would have dual use - enjoyment for when you travel there, staying in your OWN place👍🏽, but also the ability to rent it out seasonally/short term when you are away.  If it is a market that others flock to, this could be a great real estate strategy. 😉☑️😉⁣
⁣
Thoughts?? Drop a comment ⬇️below or a 🙌 if you agree!  Thanks for sharing! ⁣
⁣
___⁣

⁣
⁣

node.text:
How are you, as an AGENT, any different from the others online⁉️ 3 quick minutes to hear @brandtegic share their thoughts on the biggest branding mistakes agents make on IG.⁣
⁣
Posting content just to put it out there for the sake of volume is not going to separate you from others, in the eyes of the audience/market/customers. 🚫 Don't believe me?  Go through 15-20 real estate profiles on IG and see if you catch a trend or similar tone in copy or post. ⁣
⁣
Being different only requires a little bit of thought and effort so you can separate from the pack. 💯 ⁣
⁣
Thank you @austinrschneider for sharing your thoughts with my audience on this, brother!  Apologies for Aila interrupting you so many times, but hey, she has a lot of thoughts on this topic, too! 😂

—⁣⁣
If your conversation were worth $1,080 each, you would keep better track of them or have more of them? 💰⁣⁣
—⁣⁣
READ ON 👇🏼⁣⁣
—⁣⁣
CONTEXT - I was speaking with Rene Rodriguez of @Amplifii_influence about the metrics that matter in the sales cycle of a real estate lead and how understanding this will better help you tighten your process and value for a simple conversation. ⁣⁣
—⁣⁣
For a better understanding of this and the math that was used in sequence by Rene, please check out my link in my bio for the full YouTube video.  Pretty f’ing sure you will find it useful! ⁣⁣
—⁣⁣
**Disclaimer - I used $900K as an average sale price here only for this exercise, but before some of you reply saying you are insulted by that dollar amount OR you just wanted to jump in and correct me - remember this was an example and I understand that the average home price is over $1M***⁣⁣
—⁣⁣

🤔Think "discount brokerage," but for lending. If you know what you are doing, know what you want, and are clear on your own strategy.... then this model may very well work for you✅⁣
⁣
🙋🏽‍♂️ Most consumers- first-timers, especially- need guidance and strategy to avoid financial pitfalls that come with almost every mortgage.⁣
⁣
It's your 💰, and soon it will be your DEBT - so managing it should be entrusted with an actual human being that understands how it all works and not left up to an algorithm or robot.

node.text:
Never too young to learn about "opportunity 💰 cost."

Aila and I discussed this after she listened to a convo I had with a client about this very conundrum they are faced with. I told her here in this photo (as well as the client on the call just before this) that there is no WRONG answer to the "buy now or wait" question. There is a cost associated with both, however, 🤔

Buy now when prices remain high 📈, the market is uber-competitive, but rates are still very low to borrowers.

Wait for prices to (maybe, a BIG maybe) slow down or flatline ↔️, the market to be less crowded with buyers and more flush with inventory, but rates trend higher.

Again - no wrong answer to this, as it's always PERSONAL. Metrics and Data 📊 (in bold please: Metrics and Data), however, can help mitigate our opportunity costs.
⬇️

More household formations now than in the last 40 years = more proclaimed "buyers" in this market. Inventory still lagging, supply chains are still being reinstated playing a major role in this "lag" and it's likely to continue through 2024. The mortgage market essentially telling us to expect an uptick in loan rates as the Fed decides to commit to tapering - which is sooner than we think.

node.text:
📊 Data, Information, Metrics, Trends📉 ...... (read on⬇️⬇️).

I have to follow these constantly to provide value to my partners and clients. Otherwise, what do they need me for? 🤷🏽‍♂️

I spend a good amount of my day watching the markets, following economic trends and news 🧐. All of this helps me (not only) stay sharp on what is going on, but be able to reference and apply when it comes to providing an actual strategy.

Many lenders don't, some have no reference points at all 🚫. Others just push paper and offer rates to you. Know the difference in who you deal with.

What do you think?? 🤔 ⬇️ 🤔 ⬇️

Stock 📈 market doing great, breaking records, reaching all-time highs 🚀....but is the economy itself very strong? Working for you? Let me know your thoughts. node.text:
I've talked about having a PLAN - no matter what you're looking to do. The 𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐨𝐧 you need a plan is to 💰 GET YOUR MONEY RIGHT 💰⁣
⁣
✅ Your credit - this needs to be right⁣
⁣
✅ Your savings and funds you have built up - this needs to be right⁣
⁣
✅ Your strategy - loan product, cost structure, and timing - this needs to be right⁣
⁣
Get a plan, create a strategy, and get your 💵 right. Your future self will thank you 🙏🏽

node.text:
A lot of news, data, and movement these last 3 weeks that is shaping the narrative in housing for the rest of this year......🔥 🔥

🏠 Some inventory "loosing" becoming apparent. Albeit, its likely this will be short lived, but certain markets saw a 50% uptick in homes listed for sale

👨‍👩‍👦‍👦 👨‍👨‍👧 Demand continues to outstate itself, with more and more people "entering" the market and beginning a search.

📈 Rates took a nosedive last week, only to bounce off that floor like a 🏀 right back up the last few market days. Affordability remains unaffected by

💰 Loan programs continue to aggressively re-enter the market, spurring more creativity and options for buyers.

💵 Equity being (responsibly) accessed for reinvestment in businesses and other real estate, rippling through the micro-economy and affecting jobs, earnings, and revenue in this space (all a GOOD thing!).

Stay engaged, locked in, and teamed up with the right people watching for your opportunity and chance to make waves 🚀 🚀

node.text:
Most in my industry are telling everyone, "you 👊 need to buy now," or "if you aren't buying now, you are wasting money, missing the 🚤 ," and other comments like this.⁣
⁣
Truth is - you don't HAVE to do anything; so long as you have a PLAN. If you are intending to keep renting, what is your PLAN to invest otherwise, save towards a future home? Renting is fine, as long as there is a plan behind it.⁣
⁣
If you want to buy here in the near term, what is your PLAN to save, budget, qualify for a future home? Without a PLAN, it's all a pipe dream and may not ever come true.⁣
⁣
Any pathway in life is fine, and you don't have to own a home, have a real estate empire, or anything else you may not agree with. If you have a plan that is guiding you somewhere, in some direction, towards something......then it's all good.⁣
⁣
⁣
__________________⁣
@stevenmichaelcalabrese @candace.green_mortgage @jahleelvestermortgage @thomasbepko

node.text:
Are you one of them? 🤷🏽‍♂️🤔

Just over 70% of US homeowners have still not refinanced 😯....for whatever reason. Some were in forbearance, others challenged by job/income loss during COVID, and many have just been waiting around for no particularly solid reason.

The FED🏦 announced in their recent meeting minutes that they WILL begin tapering down their purchases of bonds and MBS (mortgage backed securities) at some point in the near future. This means that rate increases📈 would be imminent, and mortgage rates would likely follow closely behind.

Knowing that there may be only six months left of an opportunity to refinance your current loan, pull out cash, consolidate debt, etc.....are you one of 70%??

Let's talk and come up with a strategy 🤝. Follow me ➡️➡️ @arjunmortgage
